episodes.title: Money Can Suck My Cock
episodes.plot: Julian, Ricky and Bubbles each have new moneymaking schemes, Jim Lahey is on the verge of retiring and Randy has a new assistant, Don.

episodes.title: The Fuckin' V-Team
episodes.plot: Julian offers to partner with Barb so that she can keep the trailer park, but they need Lahey's cooperation over his deciding one percent share.

episodes.title: The Dirty Dancer
episodes.plot: Julian enlists J-Roc and Sarah's aid to turn his bar into a strip club. Ricky is not pleased and in utter shock when he finds out that his daughter Trinity is pregnant.

episodes.title: Orangie's Pretty Fuckin' Tough
episodes.plot: When Orangie, Ricky's goldfish, dies after being given too many shooters, Julian and Bubbles try to replace it with another before Ricky finds out.

episodes.title: Whore-A-Geddon
episodes.plot: Local TV celebrity Steve Rogers returns and rents Julian's bar for his stag party, which gets of out hand and overflows into Bubbles's Shed-and-Breakfast sheds.

episodes.title: Friends with the Benedicts
episodes.plot: Bubbles' attempts to clear up a crab infestation in his sheds and on his kitties cause him embarrassment, and he's arrested for indecent exposure.

episodes.title: Community Service and a Boner Made with Love
episodes.plot: Bubbles blames Ricky and Julian for getting him community service, so he makes them come along and help put on a "don't do drugs" show for kids. Mr Lahey gets some relief from the tablets Julian provided, but Randy finds out.

episodes.title: The Super-Duper-Industrial-Bubbles-Honey-Oil-Inator
episodes.plot: When the compressor air conditioner breaks, Bubbles has to turn his sheds into an industrial honey oil manufacturing complex to save Ricky's weed.

episodes.title: Righties Loosies, Lefties Tighties
episodes.plot: While being filmed by George Green, Bubbles gets his oil production going, aiming to make enough money to buy the trailer park for Barb and Julian.

episodes.title: Crawling Through the Shitpipe
episodes.plot: The boys sell their entire honey-oil output to Sebastian Bach, but to seal the deal for the trailer park, Julian must do something truly terrible.
